                    <body>
                              <pb n="1"/>
                              <p rend="align(center)"><placeName>Easton Pa.</placeName>
                                        <date>April 23. 1851</date>.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">The new congregation which of late
                                                  <del>arose</del><lb/>
                                        <hi rend="underline">was</hi> started in this place under
                                        the name of ,,Emanu El"<lb/> will to all appearance be of
                                        but very short duration,<lb/> since the same causes which
                                        effected the split of the<lb/> old and gave rise to this new
                                        congregation begin to prevail in<lb/> much higher degree in
                                        the latter. Not the spirit of true<lb/> religion, that of
                                        love, <sic>piece</sic> and righteousness is there<lb/> to be
                                        found, but in the contrary nothing but tyranny<lb/>
                                        injustice and irony is doing and therefore continual
                                        guards<lb/> and lamentable scandals are taking place. The
                                        conse-<lb/>quence of all this is, that this congregation
                                        cannot<lb/> get a suitable man to act as minister, three
                                        persons already <del>were</del><lb/> soho<add>?</add> had
                                        been solicited to come here and occupy this<lb/> place have
                                        declined on hearing what here is going<lb/> on, so that they
                                        were obliged to write for one to
                                                  <placeName>Ger-<lb/>many</placeName> but—in vain.
                                        What characterizes this congregation<lb/> and throws to me
                                        light over their religious principles<lb/> is the fact that
                                        their principal leader and present<lb/> minister
                                                  <del>of</del> is a man who acknowledges no
                                        religion<lb/> at all <del>and</del>; after having performed
                                        the service in the syna-<lb/>gogue he returns <del>to
                                                  me</del> to <del>go</del> his <del>grocery
                                                  store</del> business and violates<lb/> the sacred
                                        law of the <date>sabbath</date> for which he just now<lb/>
                                        had praised God ,,who has given it to us" thus
                                        evidently<lb/> showing that he has only his play with
                                        religion.</p>
                              <p>That our holy religion is thus profaned in the eyes of our<lb/>
                                        <sic>christian</sic> brethern is much to be lamented and the
                                        sooner</p>
                              <pb n="2"/>
                              <p>a congregation of this kind would cease to be the better</p>
                              <p rend="indent(7)">A     Veritas</p>
                              <p>Mr. Editor!</p>
                              <p>I request you to give these few lines a space in your<lb/> much
                                        esteemed paper <del>by</del> whereby you will oblige
                                                  <del>your</del></p>
                              <p rend="indent(5)">yours truly</p>
                              <p rend="indent(5)">
                                        <persName role="author">L M Cohen</persName>
                              </p>
                              <p>P. S. Please send me a copy of the next number<lb/> of your
                                        paper.</p>
                              <pb n="3"/>
                              <p>
                                        <addressee>Rev. Mr. Isaac Leeser</addressee>
                              </p>
                              <p>Editor of the Occident</p>
